notesStmt.note: Avraham ben Yosef ben Sa'adyah ben Avraham: inscribed with his name in the frontispiece and in the colophon, Sana, 1 Adar 1786 (folios 1v, 2r).
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: The Latter Prophets with Targum Onkelos and the Arabic translation of Isaiah by Sa'adyah Ga'on.
msContents.textLang: Hebrew; Jewish Babylonian Aramaic (ca. 200-1200 CE); Judeo-Arabic

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 2; ruled lines: 24; written lines: 24; Uniform layout. Jonah, Zephaniah, Haggai and Malachi open a new column, and Hosea commences a new leaf. The beginning and the end of the Haftarot indicated in the margin, for the most part in red ink. Masorah magna in one to three lines in the lower margin of each page. The number of verses stated at the end of each book.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Yemenite square script; Biblical text with Tiberian punctuation, Targum with Babylonian (superlinear) punctuation.

history.provenance: Acquisition: Moses Wilhelm Shapira (b. 1830, d. 1884), a antiquities dealer of Jerusalem: purchased by the British Library from him on 13 December 1879 (folio 323r).
